						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also, because of that multiplication, you can't have more than 64 metatiles (256 indexes / 4 tiles = 64 metatiles) unless you use Indirect Indexed addressing (LDA ($XX), Y).</div>
<br />Or unless you do like Super Mario Bros. and have four separate tables of metatiles, selected by bits 7 and 6 of the metatile number. These upper 2 bits are also used as the attribute value.</div>

